\": \"thentook aim\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"his rivals\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 722}, {\"ngram\": \"a body length\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 822}, {\"ngram\": \"the coveted 100m freestyle gold medal\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In doing so, the 19-year-old also broke his own world record by nearly half a second - the biggest winning margin in the men's 100m freestyle since Johnny Weissmuller, the American swimmer and actor better known for playing Tarzan, in 1928.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 1112, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1020, \"end\": 1038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Weissmuller\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Johnny Weissmuller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Weissmuller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Weissmuller\"}, {\"begin\": 1044, \"end\": 1052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999707538731719, \"rank\": 2.421701357157192e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1096, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tarzan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999952252, \"rank\": 4.829963601888379e-12, \"text\": \"Tarzan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tarzan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tarzan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his own world record\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest winning margin\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 100m freestyle\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"actor\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pan's win was the first time a swimming world record has tumbled at these Games.The pool's relatively shallow depthhas been blamed for the slow times across the sport, but Pan defied that logic with a dominant display.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pan's win\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1142}, {\"ngram\": \"a swimming world record\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1193}, {\"ngram\": \"The pool's relatively shallow depthhas\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"the slow times\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1280}, {\"ngram\": \"Pan\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"that logic\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"a dominant display\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It came in the wake ofthe Chinese doping scandal, in which it was revealed that the Chinese anti-doping authorities dismissed failed tests among its elite swimmers, blaming contamination at a hotel kitchen, and World Anti-Doping took no action.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8640799502246171, \"rank\": 0.08446671381102529, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8640799502246171, \"rank\": 0.08446671381102529, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"failed tests\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"its elite swimmers\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"a hotel kitchen\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"World Anti-Doping\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"no action\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pan was not implicated in the scandal, but that has not prevented swimming coach Brett Hawke - who is not part of the current Australian Olympic setup - from speculating on his performance.\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brett Hawke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brett_Hawke\"}, {\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9849364034937872, \"rank\": 0.014744861040428416, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pan\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"the scandal\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"his performance\", \"from\": 1753, \"to\": 1768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am angry at that swim,\\\" Hawke posted on Instagram.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1798, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Hawke\", \"score\": 0.8101299265464915, \"rank\": 0.23065130717816804, \"text\": \"Hawke\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Hawke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Hawke\"}, {\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.808104359086172e-15, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that swim\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am upset right now because you do not win 100 freestyle by a body length on that field.\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"100 freestyle\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1883}, {\"ngram\": \"a body length\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"that field\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You just do not do it.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not humanly possible to beat that field by a body length.\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 2002, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that field\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"a body length\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not care what you say.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not a race thing, this is not against any one particular person or nation, this is just what I see and what I know.\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a race thing\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"any one particular person\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"nation\", \"from\": 2106, \"to\": 2112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's not real, you do not beat that field.\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that field\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kyle Chalmers, David Popovici, Jack Alexy, you do not beat those guys by one full body length in 100 freestyle.\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2207, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chalmers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\":